{"componentChunkName":"component---src-blog-components-blog-post-template-jsx","path":"/blog/map-filter-reduce-animated/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"acc40cb5-8a66-5616-8d55-b77f1bd53be0","excerpt":"Map Animated Map, Filter and Reduce – Animated by Javascript Teacher Javascript Teacher : Twitter || Instagram || FB Notes Map Array.map – map all values to an…","html":"<p><img src=\"/6ecb7bc629794f35fb63d4e0b92c05a5/map.gif\" alt=\"Map Animated\"></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://medium.com/@js_tut/map-filter-and-reduce-animated-7fe391a35a47\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Map, Filter and Reduce – Animated</a> by <a href=\"https://medium.com/@js_tut\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Javascript Teacher</a></p>\n<p>Javascript Teacher : <a href=\"https://twitter.com/js_tut\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Twitter</a> || <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/javascriptteacher/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Instagram</a> || <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/javascriptteacher/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">FB</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"notes\"><a href=\"#notes\" aria-label=\"notes permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Notes</h2>\n<h3 id=\"map\"><a href=\"#map\" aria-label=\"map permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Map</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Array.map – map all values to an expression.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"/6ecb7bc629794f35fb63d4e0b92c05a5/map.gif\" alt=\"Map Animated\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Expression value + 1 is applied to every item in the original array.</li>\n<li>.map() returns a modified copy of the array leaving original untouched.</li>\n<li>Result: [2,3,4,5,6,7,8] (a copy of the original array is created.)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"filter\"><a href=\"#filter\" aria-label=\"filter permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Filter</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Array.filter – keep all that match a condition.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"/02e4c22c747fd22921b13a4922f53973/filter.gif\" alt=\"Filter Animated\"></p>\n<p><strong>NOTE:</strong> there is a small mistake in the animation. It should return [6,7], not [6,7,8].</p>\n<ul>\n<li>function value > 5 is applied to every item in the original array.</li>\n<li>.filter() returns a modified copy of the array – the original is still available!</li>\n<li>Result: [6,7,8] (only values that passed the condition.)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"reduce\"><a href=\"#reduce\" aria-label=\"reduce permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Reduce</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Array.reduce – reduce all items to a single value.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><img src=\"/bff71f219d322eff87c1a75b93b89faa/reduce.gif\" alt=\"Reduce Animated\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Reducer function F takes value and accumulator.</li>\n<li>In this example .reduce(v, a) returns the sum of all values.</li>\n<li>Result: 28 (the sum of all numbers in the original array)</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Map, Filter and Reduce – Animated","date":"September 05, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/map-filter-reduce-animated/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/javascript-animation-libraries-you-should-know/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"11 JavaScript Animation Libraries For 2019"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/javascript-utility-libraries-you-should-know/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"11 JavaScript Utility Libraries you Should Know in 2019"}}}}}